# Line-level union merge for append-only / generated files that almost every PR
# touches and that otherwise conflict on concurrent branches (issue #709).
#
# `merge=union` keeps both sides' added lines instead of raising a conflict.
# It is safe here because all three files are append-oriented and are
# regenerated/verified on `main`:
#   - CHANGELOG.md  — entries are appended under `## [Unreleased]`.
#   - llms.txt / llms-full.txt — generated by `make llms`; the gating
#     `make drift-check` (#522) still verifies the committed output on `main`,
#     so union-merged ordering cannot drift past the gate.
#
# After a union merge of CHANGELOG.md, eyeball the `## [Unreleased]` block for
# duplicate/interleaved lines; after merging the llms manifests, run
# `make llms` last so the committed output matches the generator.
CHANGELOG.md merge=union
llms.txt merge=union
llms-full.txt merge=union
